- For implementing our grid so far, SML / Racket style usually by column and Ruby / Java style usually by row

- But beyond just style, this decision affects what software extennsions need not change old code

- Functions
    - Easy to add a new operation
    - Adding a new variant, but ML type-checker gives a to-do list if original code avoided wildcard patterns

- In OOP adding new object is easy
- Easy to add a new variant
- adding a new operations requires modifying old classes
